```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "partition": "gpu",
    "gres": "gpu:1",
    "requeue": true,
    "job_name": "test",
    "nodes": 1,
    "ntasks": 1,
    "cpus_per_task": 1,
    "mem": "32G",
    "time": "01:00:00",
    "nodelist": "gpu[015-016,019-026]",
    "container_runtime": "apptainer",
    "container_image": "namd3.simg",
    "application_within_container": "namd3",
    "input_file": "namd3_input.in"
  }
}
```

This script uses **SLURM** to manage the job submission and resource allocation. It requests one GPU from the "gpu" partition and utilizes the "apptainer" container runtime to execute the "namd3" application within the "namd3.simg" container image. The script runs the "namd3" application five times with different output files and gathers performance data from each run.
